Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.16,0:01:33.58,Default,Kōda Miki,0,0,0,,{TIME:91169,93588}{\i1}Fanni and you\Nare brother and sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:37.38,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:95549,97384}{\i1}"Is this divine retribution?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.38,0:01:41.47,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:97384,101471}{\i1}"How can I endure\Nthis cruel twist of fate?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.68,0:01:43.39,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:101680,103390}{\i1}Fanni. Fanni!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.59,0:01:46.64,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:103598,106643}{\i1}There are things that\None cannot overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:48.60,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:106643,108603}{\i1}It's called destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:52.39,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:108603,112399}{\i1}The bonds of destiny entangling\NMine Nozomi are heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.39,0:01:54.94,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:112399,114943}{\i1}The same goes to Kōda Miki.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.94,0:01:58.40,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:114943,118405}{\i1}However, the two of them don't know\Nthe secret behind their birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.61,0:02:01.65,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:119614,121658}{\i1}I'll do my best, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.65,0:02:03.11,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:121658,123118}{\i1}I think I'll go on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.53,0:02:09.54,Default,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:123535,129541}{\fad(700,700)}— Episode 21 —\NA Cry To The Sea{NOTE:第21話\\N海に歌えば}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:09.54,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:127331,129541}{\an8\i1}I need to get back on my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.05,0:02:31.22,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:146058,151229}{\i1}If she doesn't start to study seriously,\Nno one will remember her in a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.38,0:03:02.59,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:179383,182594}{\i1}I want to become a star, too.\NBut I want to be a real singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:03.38,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:182594,183387}{\i1}Still…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.97,0:03:09.43,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:187974,189434}{\i1}Sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:10.68,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:189434,190685}{\i1}Happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.68,0:03:12.22,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:190685,192229}{\i1}Distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.22,0:03:14.56,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:192229,194564}{\i1}Only then the song\Ncan come naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:19.69,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:194564,199694}{\i1}And if it's a good song, a real song,\Nit will find its place in people's hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.69,0:03:23.78,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:199694,203782}{\i1}That's this kind of music I'm looking for.\NThat's the kind of songs I want to sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.24,0:03:30.66,Default,Announcer,0,0,0,,{TIME:209246,210664}Amido.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:32.16,Default,Announcer,0,0,0,,{TIME:210664,212165}Amido…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.79,0:03:35.37,Default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:213792,215377}Wait up, kiddo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.38,0:03:43.17,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:219381,223176}Alright. This is the place\Nwhere I make my first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:45.42,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:223176,225429}The first step towards\Nbecoming a true singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:56.18,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:233603,236189}{\i1}Unfamiliar people\Nin an unfamiliar place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.18,0:03:59.45,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:236189,239459}{\i1}This is where I'll find my song.\NNo doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.61,0:04:05.19,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:242612,245198}Good evening.\NHow about I sing you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.33,0:04:20.13,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:258336,260130}Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:22.04,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:260130,262048}We hate that kind of songs here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:22.88,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:262048,262883}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:28.05,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:263842,268054}If you want to sing, sing us something\Nthat touches your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.05,0:04:28.84,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:268054,268847}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:31.97,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:269639,271975}{\i1}Something that touches your heart…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.97,0:04:34.72,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:271975,274728}{\i1}Alright. Let's try this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:41.81,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:279941,281818}No, not like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:44.07,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:282110,284070}We told you to sing\Nsomething better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:46.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:284070,286072}What would you like\Nme to sing, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.57,0:04:52.53,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:287574,292537}Don't you get it? By something that touches\Nyour heart, he meant a war song. Duh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.53,0:04:54.33,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:292537,294331}A war song?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.33,0:04:55.99,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:294331,295999}Yeah! Don't you know any?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.99,0:04:57.04,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:295999,297042}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:04:59.75,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:297042,299753}We grew up on such songs.\NHey, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.75,0:05:01.83,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:299753,301838}Let's teach this girl\Nwhat a war song sounds like!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.83,0:05:03.50,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:301838,303507}One, two!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.33,0:05:39.96,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:338333,339960}Hey, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:45.46,Default,Guest,0,0,0,,{TIME:341711,345465}Instead of this neat stuff,\Ngive us a nice strong piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:47.50,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:346007,347509}Err…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.50,0:05:49.59,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:347509,349594}I don't know that many, to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.59,0:05:51.13,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:349594,351137}Can you give me an example?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.63,0:06:33.47,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:391636,393471}{\i1}Is there a song that\Ncan move everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:36.85,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:393471,396850}{\i1}If so, what does it sound like?\NWhat is it that people will love?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:38.43,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:396850,398435}{\i1}Nothing comes to my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:41.35,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:399811,401354}{\i1}I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:44.06,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:401354,404065}{\i1}But if I withdraw now,\NI'll be admitting defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:48.52,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:404065,408528}{\i1}Wasting my chance for the debut\Nand this whole journey will get pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.61,0:06:54.53,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:409613,414534}My only option is to sing\Nthe songs I love the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.29,0:07:09.84,Default,Mine Kazuo,0,0,0,,{TIME:427297,429841}I wonder where Sis is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.84,0:07:13.76,Default,Mine Yuki,0,0,0,,{TIME:429841,433762}Mr. Moon, please protect Big Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.14,0:07:21.31,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:437140,441311}What the heck is this?\NHow could you let Nozomi-chan do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.31,0:07:24.43,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:441311,444439}You should be ashamed\Nas her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.43,0:07:27.65,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:444439,447651}Why didn't you stop your own daughter\Nfrom going God only knows where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.31,0:07:30.40,Default,Mine Shizuko,0,0,0,,{TIME:448318,450403}I did try to stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:32.65,Default,Mine Shizuko,0,0,0,,{TIME:450403,452656}Her father tried to\Ntalk her out of this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.19,0:07:37.57,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:453198,457577}Those are the lamest excuses in the world.\NHow's that gonna change that she's gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.57,0:07:39.66,Default,Mine Shizuko,0,0,0,,{TIME:457577,459663}Shush. You'll scare the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:45.37,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:459996,465377}I don't wanna be a jerk, but you're awfully calm\Nfor not knowing where your daughter is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:47.29,Default,Mine Shizuko,0,0,0,,{TIME:465377,467295}What do you mean, calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.29,0:07:50.92,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:467295,470924}I'm drunk so maybe\NI'm talking too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.92,0:07:56.05,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:470924,476054}But when I think of Nozomi-chan, how she's\Nall alone living in some dump, I just… I just…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:58.05,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:476054,478056}I just can't stand it, y'know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.86,0:08:05.85,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:482869,485855}Egawa
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:25.20,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:503832,505208}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.20,0:08:27.83,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:505208,507836}You have unusual guests, Master…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.83,0:08:28.87,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:507836,508878}Unusual guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:31.54,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:508878,511548}I told you not to let anyone\Ndisturb us during the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.54,0:08:33.55,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:511548,513550}Yes, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.55,0:08:36.38,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:513550,516386}They told they want\Nto see you, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.38,0:08:37.76,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:516386,517762}Ah! I told you to wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.51,0:08:43.14,Default,Mine Kazuo,0,0,0,,{TIME:520515,523143}Mister, tell us where Nozomi went.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.14,0:08:44.01,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:523143,524018}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.01,0:08:46.47,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:524018,526479}Are you Nozomi-kun's siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.47,0:08:47.77,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:526479,527772}Nozomi-chan's?…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.69,0:08:55.69,Default,Mine Yuki,0,0,0,,{TIME:532694,535697}Our sis left home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:08:59.15,Default,Mine Yuki,0,0,0,,{TIME:536281,539159}You know where\Nshe went, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:00.70,Default,Mine Yuki,0,0,0,,{TIME:539159,540702}Everyone's worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:03.28,Default,Mine Yuki,0,0,0,,{TIME:540702,543288}Please tell us where she went.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:06.58,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:543288,546583}These children don't know\Nany manners. Sune-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.58,0:09:07.62,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:546583,547625}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.62,0:09:09.62,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:547625,549627}Take them out at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.62,0:09:14.09,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:549627,554090}Miki finally found some time to study.\NWe cannot waste time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:18.47,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:554924,558470}Let's continue with the lesson, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.47,0:09:22.64,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:560472,562640}Sir, what about our lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:26.18,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:562640,566186}We don't know when Miki\Nhas the time to come here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:29.14,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:566186,569147}As far as I'm concerned, nobody\Nhas forced you to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.14,0:09:30.14,Default,Kōda Sumiyo,0,0,0,,{TIME:569147,570148}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.73,0:09:33.90,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:571733,573902}Yuki-chan. Kazuo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:38.15,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:573902,578156}Your sister decided to go around\Nthe country without a clear destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.15,0:09:40.40,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:578156,580408}Even I don't know where she went.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:43.95,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:580408,583953}But having no destination\Nis what this is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.95,0:09:49.87,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:583953,589876}She left to discover the true meaning\Nof music, to become a true singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.33,0:09:51.37,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:590335,591377}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:54.88,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:591377,594881}When she comes home,\Nshe will be a fantastic artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:56.46,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:594881,596466}You don't have to worry about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.46,0:09:58.88,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:596466,598885}We must all wait for the day\Nwhen she comes back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.42,0:10:02.01,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:599427,602013}You just have to trust your big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.01,0:10:03.26,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{TIME:602013,603264}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:07.85,Default,Kōda Miki,0,0,0,,{TIME:606100,607852}A real singer?\NWhat's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:12.14,Default,Kōda Miki,0,0,0,,{TIME:607852,612148}What else could a singer want apart from\Na big stage and crowd every night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:16.77,Default,Kōda Miki,0,0,0,,{TIME:612148,616778}She just went on that journey because\Nshe's too devastated to face reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:28.24,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:626538,628248}Thank you, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.12,0:10:30.33,Default,Driver,0,0,0,,{TIME:629123,630333}Good luck, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.33,0:10:34.54,Default,Driver,0,0,0,,{TIME:630333,634546}Fuji Keiko and Kitajima Sabu-chan\Nstarted on the streets as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.54,0:10:37.04,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:634546,637048}I'll do my best.\NYou take care too, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.88,0:10:40.55,Default,Driver,0,0,0,,{TIME:637882,640552}Thanks. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.34,0:10:42.55,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:641344,642554}Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.19,0:10:56.02,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:654190,656025}{\i1}It's a small fishing village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:10:58.06,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:656025,658069}{\i1}I came pretty far.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.06,0:11:01.32,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:658069,661322}{\i1}Since I went on this journey,\Nno one's listened to my song yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:06.20,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:664117,666202}{\i1}But I still have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:09.08,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:666202,669080}{\i1}I'm sick of complaining.\NTonight I want to earn some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:18.08,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:676004,678089}Excuse me, miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.08,0:11:21.09,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:678089,681092}Could you tell me\Nwhere the closest bar is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:23.80,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:681926,683803}Miss, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.93,0:11:29.72,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:688933,689726}Miss…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.60,0:11:36.02,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:694606,696024}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.98,0:11:39.11,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:696983,699110}What business do you have\Nwith that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:41.23,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:699110,701237}I don't really have\Nany business with her…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:44.82,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:702697,704824}If you don't need anything,\Nleave her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.57,0:11:47.99,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:706576,707994}Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.78,0:11:49.99,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:708786,709996}I came from Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.95,0:11:52.58,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:710955,712582}What did you come here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.58,0:11:55.16,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:712582,715168}Just like you see.\NI'm a traveling artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.16,0:11:56.37,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:715168,716377}Artist?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:04.46,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:721591,724469}{\i1}Why does he look at me like that?\NIt's like he hated my guts.
Comment: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:06.77,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:726779,726779}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:23.83,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:740785,743830}I hope you caught many fish today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.83,0:12:28.33,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:743830,748334}But maybe my songs could\Nmake you forget your fatigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:31.62,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:750253,751629}Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.62,0:12:33.21,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:751629,753214}It's you…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:35.84,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:753214,755842}This isn't a place\Nfor pretty girls like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.21,0:12:37.88,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:756217,757885}Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.88,0:12:39.05,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:757885,759053}Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.80,0:12:40.84,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:759804,760847}Hands off me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.93,0:12:42.64,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:761931,762640}What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.64,0:12:44.18,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:762640,764183}I'm telling you to get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.67,0:13:21.47,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:799677,801471}Ah! Nitta-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.47,0:13:23.55,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:801471,803556}It's you, Nozomi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.55,0:13:24.93,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:803556,804932}Nitta-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.19,0:13:37.23,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:815193,817236}It was delicious. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.23,0:13:41.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:817236,821074}Never in my life would I have imagined\Nmeeting you in a place like this, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.61,0:13:44.95,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:821616,824952}I admire you for having had the courage\Nto decline the debut and go on your journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.95,0:13:47.08,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:824952,827080}But it seems to me that\Nit's taking its toll on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:51.54,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:828206,831542}To be honest, you significantly\Ncontributed to my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:55.96,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:831542,835963}You're an amazing musician, and yet you\Nyourself have decided to go on a journey
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.96,0:13:58.09,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:835963,838091}to discover what music\Nmeans to you personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.67,0:14:00.09,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:838675,840093}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:05.43,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:840843,845431}But I don't remember you so tanned and\Nmuscular the last time we met, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.43,0:14:07.60,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:845431,847600}You look like a fisherman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.60,0:14:09.64,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:847600,849644}I don't just look. I became one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.64,0:14:11.10,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:849644,851104}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.68,0:14:14.89,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:851688,854899}Oh, looks like it stopped raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.89,0:14:16.90,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:854899,856901}Let's go to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:33.00,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:871624,873000}Dirty and cramped, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:36.67,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:873000,876671}I convinced a local fisherman\Nto rent this hut for me to fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:38.67,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:876671,878673}Where is your trumpet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.67,0:14:40.96,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:878673,880967}I guess it's rolling\Nsomewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:44.09,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:880967,884095}So you were serious when you said\Nyou became a fisherman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.09,0:14:45.63,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:884095,885638}Yeah, I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.22,0:14:50.64,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:886222,890643}So are you telling me that you stopped\Nplaying and gave up on music?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.85,0:14:55.27,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:892854,895273}Let's sit and drink some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:59.23,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:896566,899235}What's going on, Nitta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:03.78,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:899569,903781}Nozomi-chan, I realized that more than music,\Nit was life that I wanted to discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.78,0:15:04.90,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:903781,904907}Life?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:05.70,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:904907,905700}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.70,0:15:09.62,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:905700,909620}When you work with all your energy,\Nyou learn what is joy and sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:12.91,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:909620,912915}Then you realize that there\Nis also music in a life like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.91,0:15:15.41,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:912915,915418}Here is where true music gets born.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:17.17,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:915418,917170}That's what I came to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.42,0:15:20.71,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:918421,920715}Actually I think so too, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:22.75,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:920715,922759}That's why I'm looking—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.75,0:15:26.88,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:922759,926888}Singing in bars to earn your living\Nis not what I call a real job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.88,0:15:28.01,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:926888,928014}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.84,0:15:32.56,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:928848,932560}Listen. First of all, you have to try\Nto live like a normal person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.56,0:15:37.19,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:932560,937190}How can you appeal to the common people\Nif you don't understand their lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.27,0:15:42.52,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:938274,942528}What kind of work have you done\Nup until now, Nozomi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.52,0:15:44.98,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:942528,944989}You lived in Mr. Egawa's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.98,0:15:47.20,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:944989,947200}You worked as Kōda Miki's assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:49.57,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:947200,949577}But these were only\Npart-time jobs that let you sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.57,0:15:53.33,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:949577,953331}To truly discover music, you have to forget it\Nfirst and work hard in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.08,0:15:59.33,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:955082,959337}Not that I'm the one to\Nlecture you about life, haha.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.40,0:16:23.36,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:982401,983361}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.77,0:16:26.90,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:984779,986906}Morning. Did you sleep well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.90,0:16:28.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:986906,988074}Actually…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:30.86,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:988074,990868}Actually, I've been thinking about\Nwhat you said to me all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.99,0:16:37.45,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:993996,997458}Nitta-san, please\Nlet me work with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:38.54,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:997458,998543}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.54,0:16:42.04,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:998543,1002046}Maybe I don't know how to fish,\Nbut I can at least pull up the nets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.04,0:16:44.59,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002046,1004590}Please, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.59,0:16:49.86,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004590,1009862}They're short of hands. They will hire you,\Nbut they work much harder than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.97,0:16:51.84,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1010972,1011848}I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:27.96,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046924,1047967}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.26,0:17:40.56,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1057268,1060563}{\i1}I'm fine with working,\Nbut I won't be able to play the guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:44.85,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1061105,1064859}If you don't want to work because you can\Nno longer play the guitar, just throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:52.49,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070573,1072491}What are you doing, Nitta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:55.53,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1072491,1075536}I don't care that much\Nif I can't play the guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.53,0:18:00.87,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1075536,1080875}But since I'm slowly getting used to working,\NI just thought I should continue with my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.41,0:18:02.46,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1081417,1082460}Nozomi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.46,0:18:05.88,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082460,1085880}All of us have more important and serious\Nproblems than yours, yet we keep working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.13,0:18:13.30,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1088132,1093304}Some time ago, a young fisherman named\NShingo brutally threw you out of the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.26,0:18:20.10,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1096265,1100102}To you, an outsider, it might've looked like\Na festival, that everyone was singing with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.10,0:18:24.89,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100102,1104899}In reality, however, this harbor\Nhasn't felt a bit of joy for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.23,0:18:26.90,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1105233,1106901}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:31.15,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108027,1111155}All the young people went to the cities,\Nwhere they can make a quick buck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.15,0:18:33.90,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1111155,1113908}Only women and elderly people\Nremained behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.90,0:18:37.91,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1113908,1117912}By singing, they're only trying\Nto cover for their loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.62,0:18:40.49,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118621,1120498}You see, Shingo had a lover, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.49,0:18:43.91,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120498,1123918}But she grew tired\Nof living here in poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.91,0:18:46.17,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1123918,1126170}One day, she left him to become a singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.17,0:18:47.42,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126170,1127421}Nozomi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:51.42,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1127421,1131425}You know the girl who always sits\Non the cliff and looks at the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:56.22,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133427,1136222}Her name is Akemi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.22,0:18:59.68,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136222,1139684}Her boyfriend was taken\Nby the sea during a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:02.10,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1139684,1142103}It's as if she's lost her soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.77,0:19:08.44,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1145773,1148442}She's Shingo's younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.31,0:19:14.61,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1150319,1154615}Imagine how hard it is\Nfor Shingo to live that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.28,0:19:19.20,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155283,1159203}Even so, he prefers to keep all his feelings\Nlocked up inside and continues to work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:24.12,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159829,1164125}Compared to their suffering, being unable\Nto play the guitar for some time is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:28.62,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1165793,1168629}Now I see that I looked\Nat it the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.50,0:19:32.21,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169505,1172216}You can believe\Nin one thing, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.25,0:19:38.80,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1173259,1178806}Just like you have stopped playing the trumpet,\NI'll give up on singing for a while as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.68,0:19:43.64,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1180683,1183644}But I'll never forget it.\NHow could I ever do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.64,0:19:47.94,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1183644,1187940}I can forget to eat, to do many things,\Nbut forget about singing? I just can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.27,0:19:52.23,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189275,1192236}Then try to sing without music.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.23,0:19:55.03,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192236,1195031}It's okay if nobody listens to it.\NJust sing to the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:57.61,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195823,1197616}All by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.37,0:20:06.20,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1204373,1206208}{\i1}I'm sorry for being so harsh with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:08.62,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206208,1208627}{\i1}But you're on the verge\Nof grasping something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.29,0:20:11.08,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1209295,1211088}{\i1}Too bad you're ahead of me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.08,0:20:14.63,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1211088,1214633}{\i1}It's not surprising, though,\Nas you really are in love with music.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.05,0:20:18.17,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216052,1218179}{\i1}I will sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.17,0:20:20.38,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218179,1220389}{\i1}I will sing here with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.15,0:20:40.91,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239158,1240910}{\i1}I will sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.91,0:20:45.20,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240910,1245206}{\i1}A song without music,\None that's not to be heard by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.87,0:20:51.29,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1246874,1251295}{\i1}It's possible that there is no one\Nbut the ocean that wants to hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.09,0:20:58.09,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1255091,1258094}{\i1}Let at least the ocean hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.09,0:20:59.67,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258094,1259678}{\i1}Let it hear the song I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.45,0:21:22.74,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1281450,1282743}{\i1}It's that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:24.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1282743,1284078}{\i1}She's singing my song!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.92,0:21:41.47,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1299927,1301470}{\i1}Akemi is singing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.47,0:21:43.05,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301470,1303055}{\i1}She hasn't spoken a word to anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.93,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1303055,1306934}Hey! It's a big haul!\NBring everyone in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.39,0:21:48.93,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307393,1308936}What? That many?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.10,0:21:51.60,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1309103,1311605}Yeah! It's the biggest this season!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:54.44,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311605,1314442}Alright! Ready the boats!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.65,0:21:58.36,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316652,1318362}Hey! Nozomi-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.36,0:21:59.44,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1318362,1319447}Come with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.44,0:22:00.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1319447,1320072}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:01.44,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1320072,1321449}Both of you, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:04.74,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322783,1324743}Let's go, Akemi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.74,0:22:05.61,Default,Akemi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324743,1325619}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.67,0:22:27.64,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1342678,1347641}How many years has it been\Nwhen we set out with so many boats?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:30.22,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347641,1350227}The sea didn't abandon us, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.22,0:22:33.73,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350227,1353731}We were raised by it.\NWe're the men of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.73,0:22:34.98,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1353731,1354982}We're like a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.98,0:22:35.81,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354982,1355816}Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.06,0:22:39.40,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357067,1359403}Let's all sing our song together!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.40,0:22:40.23,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{TIME:1359403,1360237}– Yeah!\N– Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.23,0:22:41.53,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360237,1361530}I know! Nozomi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.53,0:22:43.53,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1361530,1363532}Yes? What do you need me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.53,0:22:45.24,Default,Fisherman,0,0,0,,{TIME:1363532,1365242}How about you sing\Nthe lead for our song?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.95,0:22:50.12,Default,Nitta Akira,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367953,1370122}Here, Nozomi-chan.\NIt's your chance to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.12,0:22:50.95,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:1370122,1370956}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.76,0:23:09.76,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1383761,1389767}{\i1}Nozomi's passionate song has revived the will\Nto live in a girl who's forgotten how to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.76,0:23:14.10,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1389767,1394104}{\i1}At the same time, this small fishing village\Nwas blessed with a haul unseen for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.23,0:23:21.40,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1395231,1401403}{\i1}The joy and strong singing voices\Nof the sea men echoed in the Pacific Ocean.
Comment: 0,0:23:25.82,0:23:25.82,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1405824,1405824}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.53,0:23:29.45,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1406534,1409453}{\i1}Nozomi continues her journey\Nin search of the meaning to song.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.45,0:23:33.95,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1409453,1413958}{\i1}To her surprise, she's requested to sing\N"Song of Heart" in a tavern in Kyōto.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.95,0:23:40.13,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1413958,1420130}{\i1}The story of the singer Nozomi circulated from\None person to another and reached even Kyōto.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.13,0:23:44.38,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1420130,1424385}{\i1}There Nozomi meets a group of young people\Nin a rock band named The Guerillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.38,0:23:48.30,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1424385,1428305}{\i1}She ends up appearing on stage\Nin a rock festival in Arashiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.30,0:23:52.81,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1428305,1432810}{\i1}Please look forward to the next episode:\N"Nozomi's debut".
